WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:00.470
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00.470 --> 00:01.170
THEME SONG: Let's go!

00:01.170 --> 00:01.890
Peter Rabbit!

00:01.890 --> 00:05.650
Go on a run, run for our lives!

00:05.650 --> 00:09.250
We'll tear a hole in every
fence and every wall!

00:09.250 --> 00:11.000
Run through the fields.

00:11.000 --> 00:13.380
Run wild and free.

00:13.380 --> 00:16.250
And grab a piece of
every radish that we see!

00:16.250 --> 00:17.150
Peter Rabbit!

00:17.150 --> 00:18.600
Go day and night.

00:18.600 --> 00:20.570
Go for it all!

00:20.570 --> 00:22.050
It's time to fly.

00:22.050 --> 00:24.510
Come on the wind's
begun to blow!

00:24.510 --> 00:28.460
'Cause you and I, we
weren't made for going slow.

00:28.460 --> 00:29.440
Adventure calls.

00:29.440 --> 00:30.220
The game is on.

00:30.220 --> 00:30.920
Come on!

00:30.920 --> 00:31.620
Let's go!

00:31.620 --> 00:32.890
Peter Rabbit!

00:32.890 --> 00:33.630
Let's go!

00:33.630 --> 00:34.660
Peter Rabbit!

00:34.660 --> 00:35.360
Let's go!

00:35.360 --> 00:36.340
Peter Rabbit!

00:36.340 --> 00:39.800
Let's go!

00:39.800 --> 00:42.540
[GENTLE MUSIC]

00:43.240 --> 00:45.020
NARRATOR: "The Tale
of the Greedy Fox."

00:54.310 --> 00:57.250
Hmm, what do we want today?

00:57.250 --> 01:00.060
Uh, a carrot, a turnip--

01:00.060 --> 01:00.760
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

01:00.760 --> 01:02.440
[MEOWING]

01:02.440 --> 01:05.040
Maybe not the cat, Peter!

01:05.040 --> 01:05.740
ALL: Whoa!

01:05.740 --> 01:08.410
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

01:08.410 --> 01:09.110
[MEOWING]

01:12.000 --> 01:15.120
Look at those
squirmy cucumbers!

01:15.120 --> 01:16.300
Watch this!

01:16.300 --> 01:17.660
[GRUNTING]

01:19.460 --> 01:20.370
Ah!

01:20.370 --> 01:22.730
My favourite jacket!

01:22.730 --> 01:23.480
ALL: Ah!

01:23.480 --> 01:24.180
Fox!

01:24.180 --> 01:28.039
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

01:28.039 --> 01:29.980
[EVIL CHUCKLING]

01:29.980 --> 01:32.960
Mr. Todd, can we have our
fishing rod back, please?

01:32.960 --> 01:35.100
Of course, my dear boy.

01:35.100 --> 01:38.690
After all, why on earth
would I want to go fishing--

01:38.690 --> 01:41.810
when I can have
rabbits for dinner!

01:41.810 --> 01:42.680
ALL: Ah!

01:42.680 --> 01:43.550
Give him back!

01:43.550 --> 01:46.370
Mr. Todd, give
me back my friend!

01:46.370 --> 01:47.820
[GRUNTING]

01:49.000 --> 01:50.370
Lily, what are you doing?

01:50.370 --> 01:51.070
Come on!

01:51.070 --> 01:53.330
[MUSIC PLAYING]

01:53.330 --> 01:54.690
[GRUNTING]

01:54.690 --> 01:58.460
Oh, ooh, ooh, ow, ow!

01:58.460 --> 02:01.180
You'll slip up one of
these days, Peter Rabbit!

02:01.180 --> 02:04.570
Whoa, whoa, oof!

02:04.570 --> 02:05.540
[SIGH]

02:05.540 --> 02:06.500
Ha!

02:06.500 --> 02:07.220
Crab-apples!

02:07.220 --> 02:09.020
Nice one, Lily!

02:09.020 --> 02:09.729
[LAUGHTER]

02:09.729 --> 02:10.430
Yeah!

02:14.210 --> 02:15.770
Do you think we lost him?

02:15.770 --> 02:17.740
Ah, poor Benjamin.

02:17.740 --> 02:20.020
You need a big hug!

02:20.020 --> 02:22.160
I'd rather have
a big cucumber!

02:22.160 --> 02:28.270
[SNIFFING] Or how about--

02:28.270 --> 02:29.180
oat cakes!

02:29.180 --> 02:31.380
[SNIFFING]

02:32.710 --> 02:34.840
What are they doing out here?

02:34.840 --> 02:37.570
Waiting to be eaten.

02:37.570 --> 02:38.280
Hey!

02:38.280 --> 02:40.210
We can't just take them.

02:40.210 --> 02:42.060
If we don't,
someone else will!

02:42.060 --> 02:42.760
But--

02:42.760 --> 02:44.110
These hot--

02:44.110 --> 02:45.940
Sweet--

02:45.940 --> 02:47.770
Steaming--

02:47.770 --> 02:48.500
ALL: Oat cakes!

02:48.500 --> 02:51.610
[CHEERFUL MUSIC]

02:51.610 --> 02:52.579
[ALL GROANING]

02:52.579 --> 02:55.010
My tummy!

02:55.010 --> 02:56.160
Oh!

02:56.160 --> 02:58.190
Someone must've eaten them!

02:58.190 --> 03:00.050
Oh, imagine!

03:00.050 --> 03:01.370
Have you seen them?
Oh!

03:01.370 --> 03:02.210
Oh!
Have you?

03:02.210 --> 03:02.970
Have you?

03:02.970 --> 03:03.670
Oh!

03:03.670 --> 03:04.370
Oh!

03:04.370 --> 03:07.490
Whatever has happened to
my freshly baked oat cakes?

03:07.490 --> 03:08.440
Your oat cakes--

03:08.440 --> 03:10.710
What oat cakes,
Mrs. Puddle Duck?

03:10.710 --> 03:14.090
Only the sweetest,
crumbliest, oat cakiest

03:14.090 --> 03:16.300
oat cakes I ever did bake!

03:16.300 --> 03:19.780
They must have fallen out of my
basket on the way to the river.

03:19.780 --> 03:20.860
Oh!

03:20.860 --> 03:22.950
Someone did eat them.

03:22.950 --> 03:24.380
Imagine!

03:24.380 --> 03:26.120
Yes, imagine!

03:26.120 --> 03:28.980
Eating someone else's oat cakes.

03:28.980 --> 03:30.410
Mr. Todd took them!

03:30.410 --> 03:32.070
[GASPING] Oh!

03:32.070 --> 03:32.980
Oh my!

03:32.980 --> 03:34.630
Oh deary me!

03:34.630 --> 03:35.780
Oh my!

03:35.780 --> 03:38.110
Well, there's only
one thing to be done.

03:38.110 --> 03:41.710
I should have words with
that thieving fox right away!

03:41.710 --> 03:42.450
Phew.

03:42.450 --> 03:45.260
I thought we were in
trouble there for sure.

03:45.260 --> 03:47.770
Jemima Puddle Duck's
the one in trouble!

03:47.770 --> 03:50.070
She's heading to Mr. Todd's.

03:50.070 --> 03:52.400
And foxes eat ducks.

03:52.400 --> 03:53.100
[GASPING]

03:53.100 --> 03:53.829
Yeah!

03:53.829 --> 03:54.970
This is bad.

03:54.970 --> 03:56.440
Very bad!

03:56.440 --> 03:58.800
I didn't think she'd
go looking for him!

03:58.800 --> 04:00.420
We've got to stop her.

04:03.350 --> 04:05.300
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

04:05.300 --> 04:06.760
JEMIMA: Stole my oat cakes!

04:06.760 --> 04:07.840
The cheek!

04:07.840 --> 04:09.940
I'm gonna give that
fox a piece of my mind!

04:09.940 --> 04:10.640
[KNOCKING]

04:10.640 --> 04:11.540
I say!

04:11.540 --> 04:14.680
Stop making this
infernal hullabaloo!

04:14.680 --> 04:15.980
Ooh!

04:15.980 --> 04:18.089
And what do we have here?

04:18.089 --> 04:21.290
I will make a
hullabawhatsit, Mr. Todd.

04:21.290 --> 04:24.200
You ate my oat cakes
without asking!

04:24.200 --> 04:25.130
Oat cakes?

04:25.130 --> 04:26.220
Bleh!

04:26.220 --> 04:28.190
Too plain for me.

04:28.190 --> 04:29.510
I'm more of a--

04:29.510 --> 04:31.000
meat eater.

04:31.000 --> 04:31.700
[SQUEAK]

04:31.700 --> 04:34.070
Now it's no use
telling fibs, Mr. Todd--

04:34.070 --> 04:38.960
But my dear Jemima, to have
one's precious oat cakes stolen

04:38.960 --> 04:41.970
must be exceedingly distressing.

04:41.970 --> 04:45.380
Oh, it is, exceedingly--

04:45.380 --> 04:46.470
uh, ly.

04:46.470 --> 04:51.290
So please, let me cook
you a brand new batch.

04:51.290 --> 04:55.010
It's the very least I can
do for such a fair lady.

04:55.010 --> 04:57.650
Oh well, you are a gentleman.

04:57.650 --> 05:00.170
And here I was thinking
you're a no-good Nick!

05:00.170 --> 05:01.430
What a silly!

05:01.430 --> 05:02.860
[GIGGLING]

05:03.810 --> 05:07.140
[DOOR SLAMMING]

05:07.140 --> 05:09.450
[GASPING] Mr. Todd's lying!

05:09.450 --> 05:11.140
He's not going to
cook oat cakes.

05:11.140 --> 05:13.110
He's going to cook Jemima!

05:13.110 --> 05:14.080
Not if we can help it.

05:14.080 --> 05:14.780
Come on!

05:17.620 --> 05:18.570
Oh dear!

05:18.570 --> 05:21.090
I'm such a butter wings.

05:21.090 --> 05:22.260
Nonsense!

05:22.260 --> 05:25.110
Besides, for such an
honoured guest we should use

05:25.110 --> 05:27.260
only my largest cooking pot.

05:27.260 --> 05:30.700
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

05:32.909 --> 05:34.180
Ah, here we are.

05:34.180 --> 05:36.909
My recipe for roast duck.

05:36.909 --> 05:37.810
My!

05:37.810 --> 05:39.670
This pot is enormous!

05:39.670 --> 05:41.990
I could fit in there myself!

05:41.990 --> 05:44.070
Oh, you don't say!

05:44.070 --> 05:47.840
PETER: (WHISPERING)
Mrs. Puddle Duck!

05:47.840 --> 05:49.250
I need to get higher!

05:49.250 --> 05:50.730
Benjamin, stop moving!

05:53.810 --> 05:55.210
Ah, ah, ah--

05:55.210 --> 05:57.110
achoo!

05:57.110 --> 05:59.970
ALL: Woah!

05:59.970 --> 06:02.000
Ugh.

06:02.000 --> 06:02.990
It's no good.

06:02.990 --> 06:04.830
If we can't get Mrs.
Puddle Duck out,

06:04.830 --> 06:06.590
then we'll just have to go in!

06:06.590 --> 06:07.310
What?

06:07.310 --> 06:08.770
No, Peter!

06:08.770 --> 06:11.270
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

06:11.270 --> 06:12.980
Vegetables!

06:12.980 --> 06:15.790
I've never made oat cakes
with vegetables before.

06:18.440 --> 06:19.600
Ooh, don't you--

06:19.600 --> 06:22.330
I mean, don't they
look delicious!

06:22.330 --> 06:24.070
Uh, would you mind
terribly putting

06:24.070 --> 06:26.610
this orange in your mouth?

06:26.610 --> 06:28.040
[KNOCKING]

06:28.040 --> 06:29.790
What on earth?

06:29.790 --> 06:33.659
Do excuse me for a
moment, won't you.

06:33.659 --> 06:34.870
Ouch!

06:34.870 --> 06:37.010
[GASP] Oops!

06:37.010 --> 06:39.940
First a duck, now rabbits!

06:39.940 --> 06:44.640
A whole feast right
on my doorstep.

06:44.640 --> 06:46.460
JEMIMA: [HUMMING]

06:46.460 --> 06:47.980
Psst!

06:47.980 --> 06:49.310
Mrs. Puddle Duck!

06:49.310 --> 06:52.060
[HUMMING]

06:53.520 --> 06:56.950
Ah, hah!

06:56.950 --> 07:02.520
[HUMMING] And-- now!

07:02.520 --> 07:04.230
Gotcha!

07:04.230 --> 07:05.160
Where are we going?

07:05.160 --> 07:06.090
Over there!

07:08.890 --> 07:11.440
It's one of Peter's
dad's secret tunnels!

07:11.440 --> 07:12.910
Good old Peter's dad!

07:16.320 --> 07:17.790
[SHOUTING]

07:17.790 --> 07:20.510
Oh well, so much
for the rabbits.

07:20.510 --> 07:24.260
At least there's still
duck to be savoured.

07:24.260 --> 07:25.130
Ugh!

07:25.130 --> 07:27.760
Gah.

07:27.760 --> 07:31.510
Bothersome fishing rod.

07:31.510 --> 07:33.210
Mrs. Puddle Duck!

07:33.210 --> 07:33.909
[DOOR OPENING]

07:33.909 --> 07:35.360
[GASPS]

07:35.360 --> 07:37.760
JEMIMA: [HUMMING]

07:37.760 --> 07:41.050
[CHUCKLING] Jemima, really!

07:41.050 --> 07:44.050
Oat cakes must be
stirred with one's feet!

07:44.050 --> 07:45.670
Surely you knew?

07:45.670 --> 07:46.620
[SPITTING]

07:47.580 --> 07:48.530
[THROAT CLEARING]

07:48.530 --> 07:49.480
Oh!

07:49.480 --> 07:51.400
[LAUGHING] My feet?

07:51.400 --> 07:52.980
Oh me, oh my!

07:52.980 --> 07:55.120
Well, well, if you
say so, Mr. Todd!

07:55.120 --> 07:56.340
That's it.

07:56.340 --> 07:57.040
Oh!

07:57.040 --> 07:57.740
[GIGGLES]

07:57.740 --> 07:58.900
I've got to get
her out of here.

08:02.480 --> 08:03.180
Hm.

08:06.040 --> 08:06.800
[HUMMING]

08:07.680 --> 08:09.430
Peter!

08:09.430 --> 08:10.530
Oh, this is bad.

08:10.530 --> 08:12.560
This is very, very bad.

08:12.560 --> 08:15.200
With an extra helping of uh-oh!

08:15.200 --> 08:17.470
We've got to do something!

08:17.470 --> 08:18.890
[CLICKING]

08:18.890 --> 08:20.240
It's our fishing rod!

08:20.240 --> 08:21.860
Benjamin, you're a genius!

08:21.860 --> 08:23.880
You want to go fishing now?

08:23.880 --> 08:25.800
We're not going fishing.

08:25.800 --> 08:27.530
We're going to help Peter!

08:27.530 --> 08:28.620
We are?

08:28.620 --> 08:32.289
I mean, of course we are!

08:32.289 --> 08:34.429
[GRUNTING] Don't let go.

08:34.429 --> 08:36.289
Don't let go!

08:36.289 --> 08:37.429
Almost down.

08:37.429 --> 08:40.850
Hold on tight, Benjamin!

08:40.850 --> 08:44.500
This mixture seems awfully
watery for oat cakes.

08:44.500 --> 08:47.490
Mm, it's almost perfect.

08:47.490 --> 08:49.510
Just needs one more thing.

08:49.510 --> 08:51.150
The lid!

08:51.150 --> 08:52.700
Oh no you don't!

08:52.700 --> 08:55.250
You leave Mrs. Puddle
Duck alone, or else--

08:55.250 --> 08:56.760
Peter Rabbit!

08:56.760 --> 08:57.670
What a surprise!

08:57.670 --> 09:00.660
And just in time to
join us for oat cakes.

09:00.660 --> 09:02.130
Yes, Peter.

09:02.130 --> 09:03.720
Do stay for dinner.

09:03.720 --> 09:06.050
I insist.

09:06.050 --> 09:09.470
Now, I wonder who to have
for the main course--

09:10.790 --> 09:11.760
Gah!

09:11.760 --> 09:15.180
Lily, I can't hold on--

09:15.180 --> 09:16.650
ah!

09:16.650 --> 09:18.290
Eeny meeny miney--

09:18.290 --> 09:20.630
[SCREAMING]

09:20.630 --> 09:21.570
[CRASH]

09:21.570 --> 09:24.370
[COUGHING]

09:24.370 --> 09:26.050
Oh, me.

09:26.050 --> 09:26.860
Oh my!

09:26.860 --> 09:28.410
Oh, my poor nerves.

09:28.410 --> 09:30.610
And just look at all this mess!

09:30.610 --> 09:32.290
Rule one of cooking, Mr. Todd.

09:32.290 --> 09:33.640
Keep a tidy kitchen!

09:33.640 --> 09:35.320
No, this won't do.

09:35.320 --> 09:36.150
Good day to you!

09:36.150 --> 09:37.600
Dizzy duck!

09:37.600 --> 09:41.480
[GROWL] Thanks to you,
duck is off the menu!

09:41.480 --> 09:44.830
But it's a good thing
I prefer rabbits!

09:44.830 --> 09:45.640
BOTH: Oh no!

09:45.640 --> 09:46.440
Peter!

09:46.440 --> 09:48.790
He might be bigger than
us, but we're quicker!

09:48.790 --> 09:50.040
Let's hop to it.

09:50.040 --> 09:53.270
[GRUNTING]

09:53.270 --> 09:55.720
[EVIL LAUGHING]

09:57.920 --> 09:58.660
Ooh!

09:58.660 --> 09:59.980
[LAUGHING]

09:59.980 --> 10:02.440
Hey!

10:02.440 --> 10:03.620
Mr. Todd!

10:03.620 --> 10:04.490
Over here!

10:04.490 --> 10:07.460
[MUSIC PLAYING] (SINGING)
Stand your ground.

10:07.460 --> 10:09.430
You've got no time to get away!

10:09.430 --> 10:12.890
[GRUNTING AND CLANGING]

10:12.890 --> 10:14.870
Stand your ground!

10:14.870 --> 10:17.580
Come on, think fast and
you can save the day!

10:17.580 --> 10:19.420
[EVIL LAUGHING]

10:19.420 --> 10:20.340
[WHIMPERING]

10:20.340 --> 10:21.720
You can't just run.

10:21.720 --> 10:23.590
This game is all or none.

10:23.590 --> 10:27.200
You've got to use your
wits to get you through.

10:27.200 --> 10:30.180
So stand your ground.

10:30.180 --> 10:31.180
Stand your ground.

10:31.180 --> 10:34.660
I know you're gonna
think about what to do.

10:34.660 --> 10:35.650
Peter!

10:35.650 --> 10:38.140
[WHIMPERING]

10:39.990 --> 10:43.280
ALL: [CHEERING]

10:43.980 --> 10:46.290
Let's get out of here!

10:46.290 --> 10:47.610
[HUMMING]

10:47.610 --> 10:48.940
Hi, Mrs. Puddle Duck!

10:48.940 --> 10:49.640
Oh!

10:49.640 --> 10:51.810
Fancy seeing you again.

10:51.810 --> 10:54.440
We have something to
tell you, Mrs. Puddle Duck.

10:54.440 --> 10:57.170
Don't we, Peter?

10:57.170 --> 10:59.390
We were the ones who
ate your oat cakes.

10:59.390 --> 11:00.140
[GASP]

11:00.140 --> 11:01.370
We're sorry.

11:01.370 --> 11:03.530
We made you some more, though.

11:03.530 --> 11:04.880
JEMIMA: Oh!

11:04.880 --> 11:07.400
They might be a bit burnt.

11:07.400 --> 11:11.450
And please, Mrs. Puddle Duck,
if a fox ever offers you oat

11:11.450 --> 11:14.000
cakes again, don't take them!

11:14.000 --> 11:15.260
He was going to eat you.

11:15.260 --> 11:17.630
[LAUGHING] Eat me?

11:17.630 --> 11:20.240
A nice gentleman like Mr. Todd?

11:20.240 --> 11:22.240
Stop that nonsense!

11:22.240 --> 11:24.740
[CHUCKLE] Oh well, we tried.

11:24.740 --> 11:25.780
[MUNCHING]

11:25.780 --> 11:26.480
Oh!

11:26.480 --> 11:28.520
Mm, mm, mm.

11:28.520 --> 11:29.220
Yum!

11:29.220 --> 11:31.940
Crispy, just the
way I like them!

11:31.940 --> 11:34.040
[LAUGHTER]

11:39.940 --> 11:40.640
[THEME MUSIC]

11:40.640 --> 11:41.540
THEME SONG: Peter Rabbit!

11:44.540 --> 11:45.440
Peter Rabbit!

11:52.040 --> 11:53.840
Peter Rabbit!

11:53.840 --> 11:55.640
Peter Rabbit!

11:55.640 --> 11:58.090
Peter Rabbit!
